WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.381
You must understand the internal roles within Amazon. Account Managers

00:00:04.381 --> 00:00:08.761
are targeted to grow their assigned accounts' direct cloud spend.

00:00:08.761 --> 00:00:13.142
Partner Sales Managers hold targets to grow revenue allocated to

00:00:13.142 --> 00:00:17.523
partners. Partner Development Managers are evaluated on overarching partnership performance.

00:00:17.523 --> 00:00:21.903
Let's do a quick match. Match the AWS Account Manager

00:00:21.903 --> 00:00:26.284
to their primary goal. Is it overarching partnership metrics, or

00:00:26.284 --> 00:00:30.665
growing their assigned accounts' AWS spend? It is growing their

00:00:30.665 --> 00:00:35.045
assigned accounts' AWS spend. Identifying the Account Manager's specific quota

00:00:35.045 --> 00:00:39.426
is the right cue to notice.
